  <revision rev="22" vrev="1">
    <srcmd5>92a9b1b1eac58c6eae3cf7b49e9a49a5</srcmd5>
    <version>0.10.5</version>
    <time>1783015824</time>
    <user>anag_factory</user>
    <comment>- Update to 0.10.5:
  + Fix bug in Chrome pointer detection (#394 #396)
- Changes from 0.9.20
  + Update to version 0.10.4:
    - Internal Changes
      + The dixGetDisplayName() function is used to access the
        display name where available (#367).
      + FreeBSD CI testing is now performed (#379).
      + autoconf version is changed from 2.65 to 2.69 (#378).
    - Changes for Packagers or Developers
      + This version is intended to be used together with xrdp
        v0.10.3 or later.
  + Update to version 0.10.3:
    - New Features
      + H.264 capture is now supported (#355).
      + Frame capture interval can now be configured separately
        via xrdp for H.264 and RFX (#347, #353).
    - Bug Fixes
      + Fix dependency when building without glamor (#330).
      + RandR is now aware of physical monitor sizes if passed
        to the client (#337).
      + Glamor whitelist now supports amdgpu (#329) and msm
        (#346) drivers.
    - Changes for Packagers or Developers
      + This version is intended to be used together with xrdp
        v0.10.2 or later.
  + Update to version 0.10.2:
    - New Features
      + Check list of support devices in glamor (backport of
        #322).
      + Support NULL cursors and large mono cursors (#320,
        backport of #323).
    - Bug Fixes
      + Separate out key frame request from MAX_INT frame ACK to
        prevent multi-monitor screen corruption (backport of
        #288).
      + Fixes complex dirty region causing overflow of xrdp
        comms buffer (#318, backport of #319).
    - Known Issues
      + The backport of #322 can cause some working systems using
        amdgpu to no longer use Glamor acceleration (#341).
  + Update to version 0.10.1:
    - New Features
      + Switch to wyhash from CRC for capture tile diff and
        introduce lazy color conversion (#167, #301).
  + Update to version 0.10.0:
    - Highlights
      + Added Graphic Pipeline Extension (GFX) support,
        achieving higher frame rates and less bandwidth
        utilization.
</comment>
    <requestid>1363071</requestid>
  </revision>
